LABEL: DirectedConnection
COMMENT: DirectedConnection is a specialization of Connection and represents likewise the connecting element between Devices. However, the usage of DirectedConnection implies the indication of a directed interconnection.

LABEL: enters
COMMENT: The relation Enters interconnects an ingoing DirectedConnection  to its target Device.

LABEL: isExclusivelySubsystemOf
COMMENT: The relation isExclusivelySubsystemOf links a non-sharable Subsystem to its direct Supersystem.

LABEL: isRelatedTo
COMMENT: The relation isRelatedTo subsumes all kinds of inter-system relations.

LABEL: hasSubsystem
COMMENT: The relation hasSubsystem denotes the relation between a Supersystem and its Subsystem.

LABEL: OutputProduct
COMMENT: An OutputProduct is a Material that is output by a ProcessStep.

LABEL: isComposedOfSubsystem
COMMENT: The relation isComposedOf indicates the non-sharable, direct Subsystem of a Supersystem.

LABEL: Process
COMMENT: An AggregatedProcessStep representing the entire function of the Process considered

LABEL: leaves
COMMENT: The relation Leaves connects an outgoing DirectedConnection to its source Device.

LABEL: hasInput
COMMENT: The relation hasInput connects a Device to an incoming DirectedConnection.

LABEL: isDirectlyRelatedTo
COMMENT: The relation isDirectlyRelatedTo subsumes all kinds of direct inter-system relations.

LABEL: isSubsystemOf
COMMENT: The relation isSubsystemOf refers from a Subsystem to its Supersystem.

LABEL: S
COMMENT: Sample system; used for the construction of the query classes SystemEnvironment and InternalProperties.

LABEL: ProcessStep
COMMENT: A ProcessStep is a certain material processing procedure.

LABEL: ProcessState
COMMENT: A ProcessState represents the collectivity of properties of a CertainMaterialAmount  which is produced in the associating process step.

LABEL: isDirectSubsystemOf
COMMENT: The relation isDirectlySubsystemOf links a Subsystem to its direct Supersystem.

LABEL: Device
COMMENT: Devices are the crucial elements of a NetworkSystem, holding the major functionality.

LABEL: hasDirectSubsystem
COMMENT: The relation hasDirectSubsystem refers from a Supersystem to its direct Subsystem.

LABEL: isPredecessorOf
COMMENT: The relation isPredecessorOf identifies all Devices and DirectedConnections that are predecessors of the considered one.

LABEL: isConnectedTo
COMMENT: The relation isConnectedTo represents topological connectivity between System.

LABEL: isSuccessorOf
COMMENT: The relation isSuccessorOf identifies all Devices and DirectedConnections that are successors of the considered one.

LABEL: hasOutput
COMMENT: The relation hasOutput connects a Device to an outgoing DirectedConnection.

LABEL: AggregatedProcessStep
COMMENT: An AggregatedProcessStep is a ProcessStep which consists of a number of ProcessSteps in a certain sequence.
